<h1 style="margin-bottom:1em;">
    Simon Griffee <br><span class="normal">Communications Specialist, Visual Designer, Web Developer, Photographer</span><br><small><a href="http://hypertexthero.com/static/files/SimonGriffeeCV.pdf" title="Portable Document Format">↓ Download CV <span class="caps">PDF</span></a> <span class="small quiet">205kb</span></small>
</h1>

<p>
    <strong>Email &amp; Facetime:</strong> simon@hypertexthero.com<br>
    <strong>Portfolios:</strong> <a href="http://hypertexthero.com/work/">hypertexthero.com/work</a> &amp; <a href="http://simongriffee.com/stories/">simongriffee.com/stories</a><br>
    <strong>Github:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/hypertexthero">hypertexthero</a><br>
    <strong>Twitter:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/hypertexthero">hypertexthero</a><br>
    <strong>Homebase:</strong> Rome, Italy and the Internets.
</p>

<h2 id="summary" style="border-bottom:1px solid #eee; padding-bottom:0.25em;">
    Summary
</h2>

<p>
Over a decade of professional experience as communications project manager, user experience and visual designer, web developer and photographer.
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Completed projects and increased funding of international organizations through branding, user experience design and production of websites and print materials.
</li>
    <li>Saved companies time and money with good software and design.
</li>
    <li>Helped groups and individuals with honest editing.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="skillsexpertise">
    Skills &amp; Tools
</h2>

<p>
    <b>Graphic Design, writing, web development:</b> I like HTML, CSS, JavaScript, web standards and open source software, though I&rsquo;m not a luddite — if a tool is the right one for the job I&rsquo;ll use it. <b>User experience design, usability, accessibility:</b> I like fast, simple interfaces and <a href="http://hypertexthero.com/logbook/2012/04/web-design-where-to-begin/">good writing</a> over excessive style. <b>Etcetera:</b> I am also experienced with JavaScript, Python &amp; Django, PHP, Wordpress, Drupal &amp; Textpattern, Ruby &amp; Jekyll, Git &amp; Github, Apache &amp; Nginx, MySQL &amp; PostgreSQL, Photoshop, Illustrator, Lightroom &amp; InDesign, Textmate, Terminal & Unix system administration.
</p>

<h2 id="experience" style="border-bottom:1px solid #eee; padding-bottom:0.25em;">
    Experience
</h2>

<h3>
    Information Systems Officer, IPPC<br>
    <span class="normal">Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations, Rome, Italy<br>
    June 2009–Present</span>
</h3>

<p>
    Helped increase funding from donors, increase number of contracting parties to the convention and increase the general public’s awareness of the International Plant Protection Convention’s (<span class="caps">IPPC</span>) work. Provided design support and technical advice on the creation and evolution of websites and other digital media as well as hands-on design and coding work at all stages.
</p>

